1 department of military affairs must receive proposals for projects requesting funding from 17-7-133 on a
2 continual basis. The department shall prepare and submit a list containing the recommended projects and the
3 recommended form and amount of financial assistance for each project to the governor, prioritized by the
4 department. Before making recommendations to the governor, the department may adjust the ranking of
5 projects by giving priority to urgent and serious public health or safety problems. The governor shall review the
6 projects recommended by the department and shall submit the lists of recommended projects and the
7 recommended financial assistance to the legislature.
8 (2) Money from the fund provided for in 17-7-133 may not be provided for projects until the
9 legislature has approved a list of projects for the biennium through legislation.
10
11 Section 3. Section 24, Chapter 722, Laws of 2023, is amended to read:
12 "Section 24. Termination. (1) [Section 1] terminates June 30, 2025.
13 (2) [Sections 6 and 7(3)] terminate June 30, 2027."
14
15 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Transfer of funds. (1) By June 30, 2025, the state treasurer shall
16 transfer $50 million from the general fund to the local disaster resiliency fund provided for in 17-7-133, MCA.
17 (2) During the biennium ending June 30, 2027, the state treasurer shall transfer $50 million from
18 the general fund to the local disaster resiliency fund provided for in 17-7-133, MCA.
19
20 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Effective dates. (1) Except as provided in subsection (2), [this act] is
21 effective on passage and approval.
22 (2) [Section 2] is effective July 1, 2025.
23
24 NEW SECTION. Section 6. Codification instruction. [Section 2] is intended to be codified as an
25 integral part of Title 17, chapter 7, part 1, and the provisions of Title 17, chapter 7, part 1, apply to [section 2].
26
27 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Effective date. [This act] is effective on passage and approval.
